esigning networked applications. Core principles include statelessness, client-server separation, cacheability, uniform interface, layered system, and optional code on demand.\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Write an SQL query to find the second highest salary from an Employee table.\\\",\\n        \\\"response\\\": \\\"One approach is:\\\\nSELECT MAX(salary) AS second_highest_salary\\\\nFROM Employee\\\\nWHERE salary < (SELECT MAX(salary) FROM Employee);\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"In JavaScript, what is a Promise and how do you use it?\\\",\\n        \\\"response\\\": \\\"A Promise is an object representing the eventual completion or failure of an asynchronous operation. You use .then() to handle success, .catch() to handle errors, and .finally() for cleanup.\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"id\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"How does garbage collection work in Java?\\\",\\n        \\\"response\\\": \\\"Java’s garbage collector automatically frees memory by identifying and discarding objects that are no longer reachable from any live thread or static references. It uses algorithms like mark-and-sweep and generational collection.\\\"\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"The candidate demonstrated solid understanding of web protocols, REST principles, SQL querying, JavaScript asynchronous patterns, and Java memory management.\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\"}"}
