e branching, and trunk-based development. In my previous team, we used feature branching, where each new feature was developed in a separate branch and merged back into the main branch after code review and testing.\\\",\\n      \\\"scores\\\": {\\n        \\\"Technical Proficiency\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"Problem-Solving Skills\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"Communication & Collaboration\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"Experience\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"Code Quality & Testing\\\": 3\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"question_id\\\": 6,\\n      \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Explain your understanding of microservices architecture. What are the advantages and disadvantages of using microservices?\\\",\\n      \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"Microservices architecture involves building an application as a suite of small, independently deployable services. Advantages include improved scalability, flexibility, and fault isolation. Disadvantages include increased complexity in terms of deployment, monitoring, and inter-service communication. Also, distributed transactions can be challenging to implement.\\\",\\n      \\\"scores\\\": {\\n        \\\"Technical Proficiency\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"Problem-Solving Skills\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"Communication & Collaboration\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"Experience\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"Code Quality & Testing\\\": 3\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"question_id\\\": 7,\\n      \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"How do you approach problem-solving and debugging in software development?\\\",\\n      \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I start by understanding the problem thoroughly, then break it down into smaller, manageable parts. I use debugging tools like debuggers and logging to identify the root cause. I also use techniques like rubber duck debugging and pair programming to get a fresh perspective. I also make sure to write unit tests to reproduce the issue and verify my fix.\\\",\\n      \\\"scores\\\": {\\n        \\\"Technical Proficiency\\\": 3,\\n        \\\